# OSINT Village — From Domain to Dossier
## Student Materials · BSides KC 2026

**A one-day workshop in passive corporate-attack-surface OSINT.**
**Saturday, April 25, 2026 · 10:00–16:00 · KCKCC, Kansas City, KS**

Welcome. You're here to learn how to walk a public company from a single
domain name to a fully cited intelligence dossier — using only sources
that are legally and ethically available to anyone with a browser.

If this is your first time at the workshop, **open `00-Students-Start-Here.md` first.**

---

## Today's target

**Caterpillar Inc.** (NYSE: CAT) · `caterpillar.com`

A heavy-industrial manufacturer with a public corporate footprint, a
substantial physical surface (plants, regulators, supply chain), and a
federal contracting presence. CAT exercises the full OSINT toolkit —
the digital playbook *and* the physical/regulatory layer most "corporate
recon" courses skip entirely.

Full target scope and ethical guardrails: `Target-Briefs/Target-Caterpillar.md`

---

## The day, at a glance

| Time | Block |
|------|-------|
| 10:00–10:20 | Kickoff + environment check |
| 10:20–11:20 | **Module 1 — Identify** (corp footprint, EDGAR, M&A) |
| 11:20–12:20 | **Module 2 — Passive Enumeration** (CT logs, DNS, ASN, Shodan) |
| 12:20–13:20 | 🍱 Lunch |
| 13:20–14:15 | **Module 3 — Active Techniques, Passive Demos** (the toolset, the fences) |
| 14:15–15:05 | **Module 4 — Profile and Pivot** (tech stack, people, physical, regulatory) |
| 15:05–15:40 | **Module 5 — Report** (assemble the dossier, rate every finding) |
| 15:40–16:00 | Shout-outs + wrap |

**Total:** 5 hours of teaching across 6 hours of class. Each module has
its own lab. You finish as far as you finish — there's no failing
silently in this class, and no prizes at the end. The goal is the
dossier you walk out with.

---

## Two tiers — pick one when you sit down

| Tier | Color | You belong here if... |
|------|-------|----------------------|
| 🔵 **Hunter** | Blue | OSINT is new to you, or you've poked at it but never built a real corporate dossier end-to-end |
| 🟠 **Ghost** | Orange | You're comfortable on a terminal, you've done recon before, you want to automate and chase the obscure |

Hunter is **not** a separate track from Ghost. Every Hunter lab includes
one explicit "Ghost preview" stretch challenge. The goal is for Hunters
to migrate up during the day. By Module 5, many will be doing Ghost-tier
work without consciously switching.

