## Why there's a `Mirrors/` folder

When 30 people run the same `crt.sh` query at the same time, crt.sh
returns 502s. When 30 people hit Wayback's CDX API, you get 429s for
the rest of the day. The `Mirrors/` folder contains snapshots of the
most load-sensitive upstream sources, captured the night before class.

**If a live source 429s or 502s during a lab, fall back to `Mirrors/<source>/<target>.json`.**

This is a real OSINT practice, not a shortcut. Mirroring upstream
sources when you have permission and time is what professionals do.
The mirror in this repo is the lesson, not the cheat.

---

## Quickstart

```bash
git clone https://github.com/Ginsberg5150/OSINT-Village-BsidesKC-2026.git
cd OSINT-Village-BsidesKC-2026
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Confirm a script runs (keyless, no signup needed)
python3 Tools-and-Scripts/cert_enum.py caterpillar.com
```

Every script in this repo runs **keyless by default.** No API keys,
no signup, no credit cards. If a key would deepen a lookup, the script
prints the URL where you'd get one and continues without it. The
"$0 versus $500/month" line in OSINT is one of the things you're
here to learn — you don't need to cross it today to do real work.

---

## Working around blocks IS the skill

Half the value of this class comes from what *doesn't* work cleanly.
Live sources rate-limit. Tools bit-rot. APIs require keys you don't
have. Sources that worked yesterday return empty today. The web tries
to make you feel stupid.

You will hit walls. **Routing around walls is the actual job.** Every
time a source fails, your first three moves are:

1. Check if there's a mirror in `Mirrors/`
2. Check the relevant `Class-Modules/` file for a fallback source
3. Document the failure with a timestamp and an Admiralty rating — *the failure itself is a finding*

Students who finish the day with a dossier of 12 well-sourced findings,
3 documented dead-ends, and a clean methodology section beat students
who scrape together 50 unverified items every time.

---

## Scope and ethics

- **Passive only on Caterpillar.** No active scanning, no auth attempts,
  no contact with employees, dealers, or customers, no engagement with
  any social account.
- **Public sources only.** Everything used in this class is available
  to any member of the public.
- **Don't be a jerk.** OSINT can protect organizations, help journalists
  investigate power, and reunite families with missing persons — or it
  can stalk, harass, and harm. Choose the first category. Decline to
  participate in the second.
- **Know your jurisdiction.** Passive does not mean unlimited. CFAA,
  DMCA, GDPR, and state-level stalking statutes all apply. Know your
  jurisdiction and your target's jurisdiction.

Full scope details for today's target: `Target-Briefs/Target-Caterpillar.md`

